This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with community detection in dynamic networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) because the authors implemented their algorithm using Java. Additionally, it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because the paper proposes a new algorithm for community detection. It could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) because the paper deals with tracking the community structure of a dynamic network. Finally, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because the paper uses a modularity-based approach for community detection.
